---
// Per carrier dispute page stub. Phase 1 does NOT invent notice of dispute
// addresses. The mailing and dispute addresses are marked as being verified.
interface Props {
  name: string;
}
const { name } = Astro.props;
---

<div class="wrap prose" data-pagefind-body>
  <p class="hint"><a href="/take-action">Back to take action</a></p>
  <h1>{name} dispute</h1>

  <div class="notice">
    <p>
      <strong>Addresses being verified.</strong> We do not publish a notice of
      dispute address until we have confirmed it from a primary source. The
      {name} dispute mailing details for this page are being verified and are not
      shown yet. We will not print an address we have not checked.
    </p>
  </div>

  <p>
    In the meantime, here is what you can do yourself. These steps do not depend
    on any address we would publish.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Find the dispute or arbitration terms in your own {name} customer
      agreement. They are in the terms you agreed to.
    </li>
    <li>
      Keep your own records: bills, promotion offers, dates, and what you were
      told.
    </li>
    <li>
      You can also file an
      <a href="/take-action">FCC informal complaint or a state attorney general
      complaint</a> in parallel.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p class="hint">
    This page gives general information, not legal advice. See the
    <a href="/legal/action-hub-disclaimer">action hub disclaimer</a>. Use your
    own facts, in your own words.
  </p>
</div>
